description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Barts Health NHS Trust, Simulation and Essential Clinical Skills Coordinator ( Band 5) &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;22.5 hours per week over 3 days .&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are currently looking for a part time Band 5 Simulation and Clinical Skills Coordinator to provide coordinator, administrative and clerical support to the Simulation and Essential Clinical Skills Department within Barts Health. The post holder will be based at Whipps Cross University Hospital Simulation Centre . However the successful candidates will be expected to work at the other sites when requested. The contracted hours will be 22.5 hours worked over three days within the Simulation department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The merged trust has four centers for Simulation and Essential Clinical skills each of which have a proud history of being innovative and award winning. The departments are teaching areas with fully equipped simulation and clinical skills teaching facilities. The core function of this department is to offer undergraduate and postgraduate medical education for clinical skills and simulation based training. The department also provides inter-disciplinary teaching for the Trust, Universities and other healthcare agencies. Bespoke training happens in the established simulation center and in the clinical environments throughout the hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for post holders who will be able to demonstrate that they have experience of coordinating courses, and have experience of working within education. For this role the post holder will require strong organisational skills excellent written and verbal communication skills and good IT skills, inclusive of word processing. The ability to work as an individual as well as part of a diverse team is essential. The post holder will be responsible for coordinating and overseeing educational activities within the Simulation Centre, comprising full immersion Simulation Suite, Surgical Simulation Laboratory and Communication Skills Suite and Clinical Skills Lab.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;They will need to work with Clinicians of all specialties and grades to support medical education clinical skills course delivery within the Centre and at times in the clinical area. They will also have the opportunity to support Simulation Based training within the clinical areas where they will support the Simulation Leads in this delivery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;They will be responsible for coordinating the day to day secretarial/administrative duties in order deliver an efficient service across all sites. To help maintain attendance records, develop income generating courses, databases and deal with course applications, create promotional materials and be involved in the organisation of training courses and to help/support the team is key.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an interesting post and the work is diverse, and will suite anyone looking for a challenge and to be part of a evolving service within this facility. The successful applicant will be part of a friendly team who aim to deliver the very best quality service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What we’re looking for&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Someone with:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent education with good grammar and spelling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Office experience, ideally within the hospital and education setting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comprehensive reception and secretarial skills and strong organization and ability to coordinate a busy education department&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to organize and use one’s initiative&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Computer literate with accurate keyboard skills and AV confidence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to prioritise and meet deadlines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work as part of a multi-professional team and be able to work flexibly with in the job role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to liaise with clinicians regarding administrating their educational activity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technologically competent and willing to learn new skills to work with advanced teaching soft wear&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What we can offer&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Education and learning opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Part of an effective and friendly team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Diverse and enjoyable working environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h1&gt; &lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;Interested?&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information, please contact&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Simulation Lead Megan Hall- Jackson . megan.hall-jackson@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
